                                        <width>89</width>
                                        <depth>48</depth>
                                    </dimensions>.</p>
                                    <!-- Extra notes from WAS: The invocation 'Om' begins 9cm from the top of the East face and is 6 cm high. The main line is at least 11cm long and the medium height of the characters (without including marks above and below) is 1.7 cm. At the time, I thought that all of the stela may once have been inscribed. However, after checking it again in 2009 it was clear that only the top 30 cm of that single face had been polished and the rest of the surface had been left rough. I think the stela has always been known, but no-one thought there was any writing on it.-->
                                </support>
